summary: Yo dusky what do you think of Captain Marvel? (This is mainly in reference to the pathetic amount of hate she receives from fake...
question: Yo dusky what do you think of Captain Marvel? (This is mainly in reference to the pathetic amount of hate she receives from fake geek boys)
answer:
Hey there :-)

Um… as a film, I rated it pretty lowly tbh. It’s in my lower quartile for the MCU; mostly for the choppy plot points, lack of nuance and some frankly uneven acting. But I ADORED Ben Mendelsohn, Lashana Lynch and Sam Jackson in it. And Jude. I thought they were great.

I have to admit, I was a little uncomfortable with how she was suddenly being touted as the saviour of the MCU and the strongest hero even before we had even met her. My love of the MCU heroes came from journeying with them, and seeing them evolve and develop.

But the backlash from the sad cluster of misogynistic keyboard-boys ironically gave it great social currency in a way ☺️… and their useless boycotts etc show that any online discourse has almost no impact on box office or public perception.

I’m kinda looking forward to seeing her in Phase 4 as part of team-ups; and to finding out what her flaws are. Superheroes with flaws are my jam.

PS: I do reeeeallly like this new discourse about her and Valkyrie having a relationship (https://twitter.com/mcu_direct/status/1133476669161967616?s=21). That would be so kick ass.

And because you didn’t ask; here’s my current MCU ranking xx

summary: CM is exactly the opposite of military propaganda, really. On a surface level it seems like it, but it’s actually super...
question: CM is exactly the opposite of military propaganda, really. On a surface level it seems like it, but it’s actually super anti-imperialist
answer:
I think the criticism came from the fact that during the promo for Captain Marvel, Brie and the CM team made recruitment ads for the military.

The writing may not be actually propaganda but you cant deny the fact that the US military is a HUGE investor in Marvel.

And also the fact that not once the military is not portrayed heroically? It is not only the vessel for Mar-Vel’s hidden war-ending project but also where both Carol and Maria are “from”.

The only bad aspect of the military is that one guy being a dick in the 80s during her training.

Now is portraying the US military only in a good light, even if their place in the story isnt actually that important, propaganda?

Either way, I fucking LOVED THAT MOVIE
